cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the challenges of scaling up MKM to large, interconnected corpora, which involves both representation languages and software architectures. This suggests that the paper could fit into several sub-categories, including cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). However, given the focus on mathematical knowledge management, cs.LO seems to be the most likely category, followed by cs.AI and cs.SE. The use of a versioned storage system also suggests a connection to cs.DB, while the development of a modular theory-graph framework could be relevant to cs.PL.
